<p>Under a Negligence theory the defendant has a duty <strong>not </strong>to place <strong>unreasonably dangerous good</strong>s into the stream of the commerce. The plaintiff must be a <strong>foreseeable plaintiff</strong> proximately caused <strong>injury</strong> by the <strong>negligent acts </strong>of the defendant.</p>
<p>Plaintiff must prove duty, breach, actual cause, proximate cause and damges.</p>
